  "text": "After VLDLs bind to VLDLR, VLDL-derived FA are delivered to peripheral tissues, where they are used by heart and muscle for energy and in adipose tissue as an FA storage reservoir. ApoC3 impairs VLDL binding to cellular receptors, resulting in formation of small LDL particles [CITATION_1] 11) , thereby counteracting the effects of apoE [CITATION_2] .",
